<br>
Pretty much every point made as to the problems with EQ I agree with.<br>
<br>
It seems to me that people are bitter that people who just start EQ can skip all the content and effort we all put in from day 1 to get where we are and be there in a matter of weeks where it took most of us years to get where we are now. (nice run-on sentence if I may say so)<br>
<br>
I think all these problems could have been solved so very easily by doing a few simple things which I will list now.<br>
<br>
1. Make <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>ALL</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> items (gear) No Drop except tradeskill items.<br>
<br>
2. <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>ONLY</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> a group member can loot a mobs corpse. (thus eliminating random_alt92 from looting something way out of his league, also not allowing people to group with anyone 10 levels higher or lower then themselves, to eliminate grouping your lvl 1 alt with your lvl 65 main to loot no drop shit.)<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>I think that this would pretty much make people go through all the content to get to the end game.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
The other thing I would do I think Ammelen mentioned.  I'm gonna use 2 (Paludal &amp; Runnyeye) zones to elaborate when I explain.<br>
<br>
Ok, in general, Paludal &amp; Runneyeye both offer you mobs around the same level so in theory they should both yield approximately the same amount of exp.  Of course that is not the case.  Also, both these zones should offer you approximately the same quality of loot.  If this were the case everyone would have so much more content to choose from rather than going to where the phat lewt and exp is.<br>
<br>
Theres no reason to go anywhere but certain areas where the exp or loot is very good unless you are just screwing around.  Hoeser and I used to go to permafrost and just about train the whole zone to the zone in and I would use my awesome 104dd ae on them.  Now other than that, why the hell would anyone else go there, EVER.  You can get better exp in easier zones at the levels that you would actually get exp there.<br>
<br>
They focused so much on Class balancing that they didn't even think about balancing the content.<br>
<br>
Ok, I'll shutup now. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=255710" target="top">Scarboar Oh</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
